column1: Rank #3 (Only Reaseach Paper based formula)                                                                                                                                                                                                         The only formula used for sentence scoring is                                                                                                                                                                                               Wnew = Wold + (sd * (1.5*L + 0.2*d + 0.3*e)) / length(Sentence), where                                                                                                                                                 Wnew : New sentence score Wold : Old sentence score                                                                                                                                                                                      sd : standard deviantion of sentence scores                                                                                                                                                                                                            L : Number of legal terms in the sentence                                                                                                                                                                                                                      d : Total count of numeric digits (like year, case number, act, sec, rule etc)                                                                                                                                                      e : number of entities present in the sentences                                                                                                                                                                                                 Note:We haven't given higher tfidf score for the legal terms.All terms tfidf score are given based on their occurence in the document only.        Number of Documents on which scores is calcuated :7090 Documents
